messageBody:
I totally agree Terry - but in the absence of evidence at to Anthony's pronunciation, I used the more common English usage.

Moira

On 11/12/2007, Terry Smithwick <Tinyallen@...> wrote:

   Well, I've always said that the proper way to pronounce a name is the way the owner wants it.
trElIgyn

----- Original Message ----
From: John Cowan < cowan@...>
To: Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Monday, December 10, 2007 9:09:49 PM
Subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] Fw: Test message

Terry Smithwick scripsit:

>    I read your initial entry fine. (Isn't Anthony pronounced with a
>    Theta versus a Tee?)

Depends on where you live and your personal choice about it.  My brother
uses theta, but lots of people, especially in England, use t, which is
the historical value (from Latin Antonius).

--
